  "texts": [
    "The connections are sparse so that a DH-SNN model does not increase the number of parameters compared to vanilla LIFbased SNNs.",
    "S6 imply that an overlarge number of dendritic branches may saturate or even negatively impact the performance.",
    "Therefore, for solving real-world temporal computing tasks, it is wiser to incorporate the dendritic heterogeneity rather than the synaptic heterogeneity.",
    "Doing so would create a better balance between computational efficiency and the ability to model the expected multi-timescale dynamics.",
    "Generally speaking, a DH-LIF neuron has both long-term memory of the low-frequency input and fast response to the high-frequency input with reasonable computation and storage overhead, which simultaneously reflects the rich temporal heterogeneity and promises practical use in solving real-world temporal computing tasks."
